Package executor.service.service.executor

Class Action

java.lang.Object
executor.service.service.executor.Action
public final class Action extends Object
Constants class defining common action types for scenario execution.

The Action class provides static final strings representing various types of actions that can be performed during scenario execution. These constants are commonly used to identify and handle different actions in a standardized manner.

The class includes the following action constants:

  • CLICK_CSS_ACTION: Represents the action type for clicking an element using a CSS selector. This action is used to interact with elements based on their CSS properties.
  • CLICK_XPATH_ACTION: Represents the action type for clicking an element using an XPath expression. This action is used to interact with elements based on their XPath location in the HTML document.
  • SLEEP_ACTION: Represents the action type for introducing a sleep or delay in scenario execution. This action is used to pause the execution for a specific duration, allowing for synchronization or intentional delays.
  • UNSUPPORTED_ACTION: Represents an unsupported or unknown action type. This constant is typically used as a placeholder for actions that are not recognized or supported by the scenario execution logic.

The class is marked as final with a private constructor to prevent instantiation, as it is intended to be used only for storing action constants.
